SIMPLE: fustic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fustic
<hw>Fus"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>fustoc</ets>,
Sp. <ets>fustoc</ets>. Cf. <er>Fustet</er>.]</ety> <def>The wood of the
<spn>Maclura tinctoria</spn>, a tree growing in the West Indies, used in
dyeing yellow; -- called also <altname>old fustic</altname>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>fustoc</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Other kinds of yellow wood are often called
<xex>fustic</xex>; as that of species of <gen>Xanthoxylum</gen>, and
especially the <spn>Rhus Cotinus</spn>, which is sometimes called
<xex>young</xex> fustic to distinguish it from the <gen>Maclura</gen>.
See <er>Fustet</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fustigate</ent>⟦br⟧
